      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">To test hypothesis that underline is rendered so that there is a space at each end of the underlined characters ¶ underline of a  ¶ words in ¶  a sentence. ¶ underlined part of word as  ¶ some ¶ times...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">00.00.00test</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Test file</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">To test hypothesis that underline is rendered so that there is a space at each end of the underlined characters</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline of a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">words in</hi>
               </seg> a sentence.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underlined part of word as <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">some</hi>
               </seg>times happens for emphasis, as when a prefix is used, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">para</hi>
               </seg>type.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline in within a w<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">or</hi>
               </seg>d.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline followed by punctuation <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mark</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline between ‘<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">punctuation</hi>
               </seg>’ marks</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline followed by a footnote <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indicator</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is not an uncommon situation.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">underline included <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">following </hi>
               </seg>space</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">If I am correct, </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The following renderings should appear:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">no additional spaces</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">space introduced, looking like <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">some</hi>
               </seg> times and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">para</hi>
               </seg> type</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">two spaces introduced, thus w <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">or</hi>
               </seg> d</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">space between word and mark, thus <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mark</hi>
               </seg> .</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">space introduced between mark and underlined text, thus ‘ punctuation ‘</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">space between underlined text and fn indicator, thus <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">indicator</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Used real f</seg>
                     <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">ootnote</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> not a superscripted </seg>
                     <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">numeral</hi>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="">. [This to test appearance in notes.]</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">?, probably <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">following </hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>space, i.e. an additional space.</p>
         </div>
